description: After Derek Jeter is hit by a pitch and Joe Girardi is ejected, David Phelps throws a brushback pitch and both benches clear
Donaldson got hit by an unintentional inside pitch, then JA Happ retaliated intentionally
The benches clear and Jose Ramirez is ejected after he throws a ball with Jose Fernandez batting in the top of the 7th inning
Yunel Escobar, Sean Rodriguez and Jonny Gomes are ejected when benches clear after Escobar steals third base with a five-run lead
Following Hector Rondon's pitch inside to Jeff Francoeur, tensions escalate and the benches empty in the top of the 9th inning
The benches clear and A.J. Cole is ejected after he throws a ball behind Jung Ho Kang in the bottom of the 3rd inning
Jackie Bradley Jr. fields a ball off the wall in center and fires to third to cut down Chase Headley, then the benches clear in the 7th
After Yasiel Puig grounds out to Madison Bumgarner, the two exchange words and the benches clear in the bottom of the 7th inning
Benches clear after Reed Johnson swings and is hit with the pitch and both Casey McGehee and Mike Redmond are ejected in the 5th
Tyler Anderson is ejected from the game after hitting Maikel Franco with a pitch, prompting the benches to clear in the bottom of the 4th
Manny Machado is hit by a pitch by Yordano Ventura and a benches-clearing altercation ensues in the bottom of the 5th inning
Junior Lake belts a two-run home run in the 6th, and then the benches clear after Lake and J.T. Realmuto exchange words at home
After Carlos Gomez gets emotional near home plate after a flyout, the Astros and Yankees' benches clear
Yasiel Puig is plunked by Adam Wainwright, causing benches to clear as the two clubs have history dating back to last year's NLCS
Roberto Osuna induces a lineout from Steven Souza Jr. to end the game and notch the save, then both benches come out on to the field
Rougned Odor and Hank Conger exchange words at the plate, forcing the benches to clear in the 9th inning
Both benches clear after Mike Carp is hit by a pitch from David Price, and Red Sox bench coach Torey Lovullo is ejected
Hansel Robles and Terry Collins are ejected after his pitch goes up and in on Cameron Rupp, causing the benches to clear in the 6th
Albert Pujols rips an RBI single into center field and the benches clear after Mike Trout hustles home to score
Carlos Gomez hits a homer off Paul Maholm and benches clear after Gomez exchanges words with Freddie Freeman, Brian McCann and several Braves players.
Tony Watson hits Brandon Phillips on the wrist in the 8th inning, resulting in both benches clearing and three ejections
Matt Kemp gets upset after being hit by a Julio Teheran pitch, which leads to the benches clearing in the 1st inning
After a pickoff attempt, Asdrubal Cabrera and Adam Rosales exchange words, leading to the benches clearing in the 4th inning
Yordano Ventura and Adam Eaton argue while walking off the field, prompting benches to clear and tempers to flare
Larry Bowa gets upset after a quick pitch from Hansel Robles and gets ejected as the benches clear
Marlins rookie Jose Fernandez hits his first career homer, but the Braves take exception as he admires the blast, which causes the benches to clear.
The benches clear in the 8th inning after Aaron Sanchez is ejected for hitting Alcides Escobar with a pitch
Tempers flare causing benches to clear
Denard Span hits an RBI groundout but takes exception to Cliff Lee's earlier quick close-pitch, causing the benches to clear
Archie Bradley and Rich Hill exchange words after Hill grounds out, prompting benches to clear
Luis Severino hits Justin Smoak and the benches clear again in the bottom of the 2nd inning, as Severino is ejected from the game
The Tigers and Indians have a heated exchange fueled by Gary Sheffield getting hit by a pitch
Josh Osich hits David Peralta with a pitch for the second time in as many days, causing both dugouts to empty in the 8th inning
Gregg, Papi exchange words as benches clear
Mark Teixeira has words for Steven Matz after being hit by a pitch, prompting the benches to clear in the 8th inning
Benches clear and tempers flare after Bautista has a hard slide into second baseman Rougned Odor.
Dodgers pitcher Chan Ho Park goes after Angels pitcher Tim Belcher after Park's bunt in the bottom of the 5th
Red Sox, Indians exchange heated words
David Ross takes a couple high-and-tight pitches while attempting to bunt, admonishes Bud Norris and the benches briefly clear
Victor Martinez is hit by a Chris Sale pitch in the 6th, after which the benches clear and the teams exchange words
After Madison Bumgarner strikes out Wil Myers, they exchange words and tempers flare, causing both benches to clear
Brett Lawrie slides hard into second, injuring Alcides Escobar's left knee and emptying the benches on a play that is reviewed
Vin Scully walks us through all the on-field commotion after Zack Greinke plunks Carlos Quentin and the benches clear in Dodgers-Padres game.
Crazy fight between Nationals and Marlins
A.J. Pierzynski barrels into Michael Barrett to score on a sac fly, causing Barrett to react and both White Sox and Cubs benches to clear.
In one of the most infamous bench-clearing incidents in MLB history, Robin Ventura charges the mound after being hit by Nolan Ryan.
After a close pitch from Pedro Martinez to Karim Garcia, Manny Ramirez takes exception to a Roger Clemens pitch and benches clear. Don Zimmer winds up on the ground.
Alex Rodriguez and Jason Varitek fight, leading to both Yankees and Red Sox benches and bullpens clearing.
In the bottom of the eighth, Craig Lefferts hits Pascual Perez, causing both benches to clear.
